org.teatrove.trove.util
Class ConcurrentLinkedList<E>

java.lang.Object
  org.teatrove.trove.util.ConcurrentLinkedList<E>

public class ConcurrentLinkedList<E>
extends Object

This class implements a thread safe queue. It differs from the LinkedList and Queue implementations in java.util.concurrent in that there is an implementation of the remove method that runs in constant time (vs. the typical linear time implementation that exists in the java.util.concurrent libraries). IMPORTANT NOTE: Once a Node reference has been passed into the remove() call, its reference should be promptly discarded.

Author:

Method Detail

offerAndGetNode

public ConcurrentLinkedList.Node<E> offerAndGetNode(E e)
Add a new item to the tail of the queue and return a Node reference. This reference can be used as a handle that can be passed to remove(Node) where constand time removes are necessary. Calls to this method and poll() do not mutually block, however, concurrent calls to this method are serialized.

size

public int size()
Retrieves the current queue length. This is a non-blocking operation.

clear

public void clear()
Clears the contents of the queue. This is a blocking operation.

remove

public boolean remove(ConcurrentLinkedList.Node<E> e)
Removes a given Node handle. This is a blocking operation that runs in constant time.

poll

public E poll()
Removes and returns the item at the head of the queue. Concurrent calls to this method and offerAndGetNode() do not mutually block, however, concurrent calls to this method are serialized.
